namespace Java.Io

Contains .NET proxy types for Java classes from the package java.io.

See:
          Description

Type Summary
Closeable .NET proxy type for interface java.io.Closeable.
A Closeable is a source or destination of data that can be closed.
FilterOutputStream .NET proxy type for class java.io.FilterOutputStream.
This class is the superclass of all classes that filter output streams.
Flushable .NET proxy type for interface java.io.Flushable.
A Flushable is a destination of data that can be flushed.
InputStream .NET proxy type for class java.io.InputStream.
This abstract class is the superclass of all classes representing an input stream of bytes.
OutputStream .NET proxy type for class java.io.OutputStream.
This abstract class is the superclass of all classes representing an output stream of bytes.
PrintStream .NET proxy type for class java.io.PrintStream.
A PrintStream adds functionality to another output stream, namely the ability to print representations of various data values conveniently.
PrintWriter .NET proxy type for class java.io.PrintWriter.
Prints formatted representations of objects to a text-output stream.
Reader .NET proxy type for class java.io.Reader.
Abstract class for reading character streams.
Serializable .NET proxy type for interface java.io.Serializable.
Serializability of a class is enabled by the class implementing the java.io.Serializable interface.
Writer .NET proxy type for class java.io.Writer.
Abstract class for writing to character streams.
